Are you crazy? You killed Wild Tiger.

107
00:08:21.584 --> 00:08:25.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, no. Barnaby is
responsible for his death!

108
00:08:25.714 --> 00:08:28.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't forget...
I can control people's memories,

109
00:08:28.425 --> 00:08:29.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they'll believe what I want them to.

110
00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:33.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

111
00:08:34.222 --> 00:08:35.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ngh!

112
00:08:36.224 --> 00:08:38.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Agnes] <i>Hello, heroes!</i>

113
00:08:38.268 --> 00:08:41.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We recorded everything you</i>
<i>just said, Mr. Maverick!</i>

114
00:08:41.438 --> 00:08:43.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I didn't know you were</i>
<i>so thoroughly corrupt!</i>

115
00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:45.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But... Your memory!

116
00:08:45.358 --> 00:08:48.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry about that. Did I forget
to tell you? Well, surprise!

117
00:08:49.863 --> 00:08:53.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Unfortunately for you,</i>
<i>I actually did see that white burst.</i>

118
00:08:57.996 --> 00:08:59.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The truth is I was
really worried.

119
00:08:59.956 --> 00:09:03.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wasn't sure what you'd do to me
if you found out I got my memory back.

120
00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:06.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I have to say, the toughest part</i>
<i>of the whole process</i>

121
00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:09.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>was trying to restore communications</i>
<i>without you finding out.</i>

122
00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:10.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Damn you!

123
00:09:10.675 --> 00:09:14.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can see you're upset.
But truthfully, I have to thank you...

124
00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:17.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The ratings for this particular show
have gone right through the roof!

125
00:09:17.432 --> 00:09:18.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

126
00:09:18.767 --> 00:09:20.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Oh, yes, Mr. Maverick.</i>

127
00:09:20.769 --> 00:09:25.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>The fact is, almost everyone</i>
<i>in Stern Bild is seeing this right now.</i>

128
00:09:26.149 --> 00:09:32.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[giggles] <i>Our ratings are going to be</i>
<i>absolutely astronomical!</i>

129
00:09:32.155 --> 00:09:34.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I wish you could see</i>
<i>the look on your face!</i>

130
00:09:34.991 --> 00:09:37.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>We've got the whole</i>
<i>thing on close-up!</i>

131
00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:39.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's time to surrender!

132
00:09:42.123 --> 00:09:44.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This guy has no idea
when to quit!

133
00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:53.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no place for you to hide,
Maverick! You might as well give up!

134
00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:56.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Maverick]
Don't be so sure about that!

135
00:10:07.273 --> 00:10:08.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[chuckles]

136
00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:17.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Watch it. Any sudden moves on your part,
and this girl is dead!

137
00:10:17.826 --> 00:10:18.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kaede...

138
00:10:21.955 --> 00:10:22.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Right on time.

139
00:10:23.081 --> 00:10:25.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be taking your
helicopter, Agnes.

140
00:10:29.003 --> 00:10:30.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

141
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:31.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh my god!

142
00:10:40.723 --> 00:10:43.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've come back from
the depths of hell!

143
00:10:46.729 --> 00:10:48.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uhh.. Heh.

144
00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:50.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Guess that line was a
little over the top, huh?

145
00:10:51.985 --> 00:10:54.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was debating between
that one and this one...

146
00:10:54.404 --> 00:10:56.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't you worry,
Tiger's back!

147
00:10:56.865 --> 00:10:58.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kotetsu? You're okay!

148
00:10:59.159 --> 00:11:00.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

149
00:11:01.286 --> 00:11:03.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you were dead!
I saw you stop breathing!

150
00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:05.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on man,
give me some credit.

151
00:11:05.707 --> 00:11:08.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I couldn't stand it,
and passed out from all the pain.

152
00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:10.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you even
check my pulse?

153
00:11:11.254 --> 00:11:12.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey! What's
with you?

154
00:11:12.714 --> 00:11:15.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, Dad...
Dad...

155
00:11:15.466 --> 00:11:18.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tiger! Thank goodness!
I can't believe it!

156
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:20.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, what's going on?

157
00:11:20.138 --> 00:11:21.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on, are you nuts?

158
00:11:21.639 --> 00:11:23.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not nice to
make girls cry. [sobs]

159
00:11:24.100 --> 00:11:25.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome back.

160
00:11:25.101 --> 00:11:26.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome back, again!

161
00:11:26.436 --> 00:11:27.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huuut!

162
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:29.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing?!

163
00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:31.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stop!

164
00:11:33.151 --> 00:11:36.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Maverick...
That's pretty lame of you.

165
00:11:36.404 --> 00:11:40.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How could you? I devoted my life
to avenging my parents' murder.

166
00:11:40.408 --> 00:11:42.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
At times, it became my
only reason for living!

167
00:11:45.330 --> 00:11:49.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to pay for that!
And all the other crimes you've committed!

168
00:11:49.751 --> 00:11:54.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Crimes? Really, what crimes
have I actually committed?

169
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:55.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What.

170
00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:59.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks to all my efforts,
the public has come to accept heroes.

171
00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:02.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And because of that,
you're able to live your lives freely.

172
00:12:02.722 --> 00:12:04.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That doesn't give
you a free pass!

173
00:12:04.557 --> 00:12:06.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Maverick]
Before Hero TV came along,

174
00:12:06.809 --> 00:12:09.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you weren't seen as the symbols
of justice you are today.

175
00:12:10.980 --> 00:12:12.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The public needed a sense of hope.

176
00:12:13.024 --> 00:12:16.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And watching you capture low-level
criminals provided that.

177
00:12:17.487 --> 00:12:19.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I gave the people exactly
what they needed!

178
00:12:19.697 --> 00:12:21.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah, so you and your cronies
could run this place!

179
00:12:22.367 --> 00:12:26.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Maverick] <i>And what's so bad about that?</i>
<i>Someone has to be in charge!</i>

180
00:12:26.412 --> 00:12:28.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Stern Bild used to</i>
<i>be a run-down dump.</i>

181
00:12:28.748 --> 00:12:32.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The sense of security that the Heroes</i>
<i>provided has turned things around,</i>

182
00:12:32.293 --> 00:12:34.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and made this city</i>
<i>what it is today!</i>

183
00:12:34.921 --> 00:12:37.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Without me, this place
would not have progressed.

184
00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I did what needed
to be done!

185
00:12:39.217 --> 00:12:40.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You should be thanking me,
not arresting me!

186
00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:45.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nice try, Maverick,
but you're finished here!

187
00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:47.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And your Ouroboros.

188
00:12:47.850 --> 00:12:49.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ouroboros will go on.

189
00:12:51.145 --> 00:12:53.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What? But aren't you
the boss of Ouroboros?

190
00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:56.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You understand so little...

191
00:12:56.526 --> 00:12:57.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Guess I have no choice.

192
00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:03.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey! What are you
talking about?

193
00:13:04.075 --> 00:13:05.285 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Barnaby] <i>What do you mean?!</i>

194
00:13:05.368 --> 00:13:06.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

195
00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:32.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, Kaede.
That was scary, wasn't it?

196
00:13:34.022 --> 00:13:35.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's okay, Dad,
you were awesome!

197
00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:38.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ben]
Wow, I can't believe it!

198
00:13:38.901 --> 00:13:41.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Heh heh, Kotetsu,
you're alive!

199
00:13:42.864 --> 00:13:44.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But then, why did
we lose his signal?

200
00:13:45.033 --> 00:13:48.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We lost his signal because</i>
<i>his suit got destroyed.</i>

201
00:13:48.244 --> 00:13:50.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, who cares?
I'm just glad you're alive, buddy.

202
00:13:50.913 --> 00:13:51.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Agh, stop it, will ya? That hurts!

203
00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:53.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here...

204
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:54.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is this?

205
00:13:55.877 --> 00:13:59.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Any idea on the meaning</i>
<i>behind these numbers?</i>

206
00:13:59.172 --> 00:14:02.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Your parents used it as the password</i>
<i>to activate the safety mode.</i>

207
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:03.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

208
00:14:04.093 --> 00:14:06.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I see. If it helps at all,</i>

209
00:14:06.304 --> 00:14:08.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>you need to know your parents</i>
<i>protected you today.</i>

210
00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Be grateful to them.</i>

211
00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:13.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I always am in my heart.

212
00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:15.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But was I really able
to avenge them?

213
00:14:15.980 --> 00:14:16.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What?</i>

214
00:14:17.148 --> 00:14:19.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I still don't know the
truth behind all this.

215
00:14:22.236 --> 00:14:25.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey! We captured the bad guy,
so let's call it a win!

216
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:28.534 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Also, this made you
guys even more popular!

217
00:14:28.618 --> 00:14:30.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're gonna have to start
working a lot harder now!

218
00:14:31.079 --> 00:14:34.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Okay! I know we will be successful,
as long as we stick together!

219
00:14:34.582 --> 00:14:35.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I agree!
-Mm-hmm!

220
00:14:41.172 --> 00:14:42.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take care of things,
for my sake.

221
00:14:43.091 --> 00:14:44.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[all] What?

222
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:46.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be with you all in spirit.

223
00:14:46.427 --> 00:14:47.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you
talking about?

224
00:14:48.054 --> 00:14:49.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm giving up the
hero business.

225
00:14:49.931 --> 00:14:51.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps of confusion]

226
00:14:52.183 --> 00:14:54.811 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just don't know just how
long my powers will last.

227
00:14:54.894 --> 00:14:56.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, my biggest
dream came true.

228
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My daughter thinks
I'm awesome!

229
00:14:59.148 --> 00:15:00.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then I'm retiring, too.

230
00:15:00.882 --> 00:15:01.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

231
00:15:02.026 --> 00:15:05.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no point in being a hero
without my partner, Kotetsu.

232
00:15:05.238 --> 00:15:06.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hold it!
Wait a second!

233
00:15:06.948 --> 00:15:08.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This was all part of Maverick's plan.

234
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:11.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He set the whole thing up
so I'd become a Hero.

235
00:15:13.162 --> 00:15:16.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
From now on, I just want to live life,
making my own choices.

236
00:15:26.300 --> 00:15:28.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[screeching stop]

237
00:15:28.553 --> 00:15:30.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What the hell...?!
-What's going on?

238
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:31.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gunshots]

239
00:15:31.556 --> 00:15:32.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're under attack!

240
00:15:33.224 --> 00:15:34.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[machine guns firing]

241
00:15:34.809 --> 00:15:36.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bodies dropping]

242
00:15:43.234 --> 00:15:45.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Listen to me,
Albert Maverick!

243
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:48.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No one can escape
from their sins!

244
00:15:49.407 --> 00:15:52.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hear the voice of Thanatos!

245
00:15:57.248 --> 00:15:59.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
ONE YEAR LATER

246
00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:05.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
John!

247
00:16:05.381 --> 00:16:06.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Slow down, buddy!

248
00:16:14.056 --> 00:16:15.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This feels weird.

249
00:16:16.559 --> 00:16:19.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm thinking of incorporating
this into my routine.

250
00:16:22.356 --> 00:16:24.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grah! Hey, cut that out!

251
00:16:24.233 --> 00:16:27.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's the matter, your booty
can't take the heat? [chuckles]

252
00:16:29.447 --> 00:16:30.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look at this, Karina!

253
00:16:30.573 --> 00:16:31.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

254
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:32.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Blue Rose just
released a new single!

255
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:33.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh...

256
00:16:33.951 --> 00:16:35.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just bought it myself!

257
00:16:35.286 --> 00:16:37.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hear she writes the music
and lyrics all on her own.

258
00:16:37.830 --> 00:16:39.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can borrow
it sometime.

259
00:16:39.332 --> 00:16:41.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks. That'd be great.

260
00:16:42.668 --> 00:16:43.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[phone buzzing]

261
00:16:43.878 --> 00:16:46.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry. I gotta get going!

262
00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:48.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
John, we're supposed
to be going home.

263
00:16:48.758 --> 00:16:50.384 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks for the dress, mom!

264
00:16:50.551 --> 00:16:53.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks! I'll visit soon!

265
00:16:53.921 --> 00:16:55.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Duty calls!

266
00:16:55.431 --> 00:16:56.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, wait for me!

267
00:16:56.849 --> 00:16:58.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello there, all you heroes.

268
00:16:58.684 --> 00:17:01.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The criminal you're after
is in the Medaille Area.

269
00:17:01.395 --> 00:17:03.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let's capture both
him and some ratings!

270
00:17:09.278 --> 00:17:12.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[announcer] <i>Good evening,</i>
<i>and welcome to Hero TV!</i>

271
00:17:12.949 --> 00:17:17.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Our six Heroes are in pursuit of</i>
<i>a dangerous criminal, even as we speak!</i>

272
00:17:35.596 --> 00:17:37.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry I haven't
come to visit you.

273
00:17:38.349 --> 00:17:40.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been trying to
sort some things out.

274
00:17:41.477 --> 00:17:44.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But, it's the anniversary of your death.

275
00:17:49.443 --> 00:17:51.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I miss you both,
Mom and Dad...

276
00:17:53.155 --> 00:17:55.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wish I could have spent
more time with you.

277
00:18:00.496 --> 00:18:01.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

278
00:18:04.709 --> 00:18:07.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Saito] <i>Any idea on the meaning</i>
<i>behind these numbers?</i>

279
00:18:14.218 --> 00:18:15.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's the matter, mom?

280
00:18:15.636 --> 00:18:19.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can count on your dad and me
to protect you forever and ever.

281
00:18:20.349 --> 00:18:24.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And in return, we ask that you strive
to be kind and protect others.

282
00:18:26.522 --> 00:18:29.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mom... Dad...
[sobbing]

283
00:18:34.947 --> 00:18:36.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The brakes aren't working!

284
00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:37.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yaaah!

285
00:18:40.202 --> 00:18:41.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>It's all over, boys!</i>

286
00:18:41.829 --> 00:18:45.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>My ice is a little cold, but your crime</i>
<i>has been completely put on hold!</i>

287
00:18:46.167 --> 00:18:49.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[announcer]
<i>Another quick arrest made by Blue Rose!</i>

288
00:18:49.170 --> 00:18:50.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Magnificent!</i>

289
00:18:50.171 --> 00:18:51.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How did she do that?!
-She beat us here.

290
00:18:51.756 --> 00:18:52.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Damn it!

291
00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:53.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's first again?

292
00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:54.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stop right there!

293
00:18:55.092 --> 00:18:56.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

294
00:18:56.886 --> 00:18:58.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[announcer]
<i>What's happening now?</i>

295
00:18:58.554 --> 00:19:00.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>The Second League Heroes</i>
<i>are after someone!</i>

296
00:19:00.806 --> 00:19:02.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You won't escape!

297
00:19:02.099 --> 00:19:03.893 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Look, it's Wild Tiger!</i>

298
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:05.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come back here!

299
00:19:05.853 --> 00:19:08.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>At one point, Tiger retired from</i>
<i>the hero business,</i>

300
00:19:08.272 --> 00:19:10.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>due to his declining powers.</i>

301
00:19:10.149 --> 00:19:12.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>But now, calling himself</i>
<i>'Wild Tiger One-Minute',</i>

302
00:19:12.985 --> 00:19:15.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>he has enthusiastically</i>
<i>returned to active duty!</i>

303
00:19:15.905 --> 00:19:17.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He's not kidding around, either.</i>

304
00:19:17.406 --> 00:19:19.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We're told his power lasts for</i>
<i>just one minute!</i>

305
00:19:19.909 --> 00:19:23.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And he's not afraid to hide it!</i>
<i>I gotta tell you, he is the man!</i>

306
00:19:23.954 --> 00:19:25.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grandma, did you see?

307
00:19:25.331 --> 00:19:27.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dad's on TV,
and he looks good!

308
00:19:27.124 --> 00:19:28.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? Is he keeping up?

309
00:19:29.210 --> 00:19:32.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[announcer] <i>Well that's it for us!</i>
<i>Tune in next time!</i>

310
00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aw, The show's over!

311
00:19:35.466 --> 00:19:37.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't they give the Second
League Heroes some air-time?

312
00:19:37.885 --> 00:19:39.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not fair!

313
00:19:39.553 --> 00:19:42.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
'Wild Tiger One-Minute'.
What a name.

314
00:19:42.264 --> 00:19:44.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who thinks this stuff up?

315
00:19:44.141 --> 00:19:45.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

316
00:19:45.184 --> 00:19:46.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ah!

317
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:49.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thanks for coming in.
Can you sign off on this?

318
00:19:53.776 --> 00:19:55.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you kindly.

319
00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:56.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

320
00:19:57.738 --> 00:19:59.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah, looks like you're
already needed, sir.

321
00:20:00.074 --> 00:20:01.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

322
00:20:02.618 --> 00:20:05.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Saito, old buddy!
Try to talk a little louder, will ya?!

323
00:20:05.830 --> 00:20:07.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whispering]

324
00:20:08.249 --> 00:20:10.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Alright pal,
turn yourself in.

325
00:20:10.626 --> 00:20:13.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I happen to know you
already exhausted your powers,

326
00:20:13.295 --> 00:20:14.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so you can't stop me!

327
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:15.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

328
00:20:15.840 --> 00:20:17.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't be a smart-ass!

329
00:20:17.425 --> 00:20:20.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can take you down,
powers or no powers--

330
00:20:20.219 --> 00:20:24.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps, screams]

331
00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:37.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bunny?

332
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:40.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Honestly. You haven't
changed a bit, have you?

333
00:20:40.489 --> 00:20:42.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What brings you here?
I thought you retired.

334
00:20:42.992 --> 00:20:45.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really? I should ask
you the same thing.

335
00:20:45.244 --> 00:20:46.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, yeah.

336
00:20:46.746 --> 00:20:50.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well Kaede said I was uncool
for being a couch potato all day long.

337
00:20:51.250 --> 00:20:53.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you know what I realized?

338
00:20:53.127 --> 00:20:56.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't always get to set your own
limits with the choices you make.

339
00:20:57.882 --> 00:20:59.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So that's that.

340
00:20:59.091 --> 00:21:00.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Even if I lose
all my powers,

341
00:21:00.885 --> 00:21:02.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm still gonna
keep on trying.

342
00:21:03.512 --> 00:21:05.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And even if I look
ridiculous,

343
00:21:05.723 --> 00:21:07.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm gonna remain a
Hero 'til the very end.

344
00:21:07.975 --> 00:21:09.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll never give up.

345
00:21:09.977 --> 00:21:13.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When you think about it, it doesn't hurt
to have a Hero who's uncool, right?

346
00:21:14.732 --> 00:21:16.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now I've heard everything.

347
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:19.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you're gonna make a comeback,
then I suppose I'll have to, as well.

348
00:21:19.695 --> 00:21:20.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And why's that?

349
00:21:20.946 --> 00:21:24.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you mean?
Because I'm your partner, that's why.

350
00:21:24.700 --> 00:21:25.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

351
00:21:25.701 --> 00:21:28.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I have to advise you. You'll probably
have to pay for these damages.

352
00:21:28.996 --> 00:21:30.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, wait a minute!

353
00:21:30.247 --> 00:21:32.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not the one who suddenly appeared
and smashed this hood!

354
00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:35.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So you should pay to
have this car repaired!

355
00:21:35.419 --> 00:21:36.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How could you possibly
figure that?

356
00:21:37.087 --> 00:21:40.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Easy! Whose feet actually landed
on the hood and caved it in?

357
00:21:40.508 --> 00:21:41.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're unbelievable!

358
00:21:41.509 --> 00:21:42.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[growling]

359
00:21:43.636 --> 00:21:46.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Okay. It's time to
go now, old man.

360
00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:49.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I read you... L'il bunny.

361
00:21:51.769 --> 00:21:55.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think it's time...
to let out a Wild Roar!

